About Pincode 380001

PIN code 380001 consisits of 6 digit code which is used to find out post offices in district in India. The first digit of a PIN indicates the zone (Northern/ Western/ Southern/ Eestern). For the pincode 380001, first digit is "3" so zone is Western. The second digit indicates the sub-zone. Here combination of first two digit is "38" So this denotes to the state Gujarat, and the third, combined with the first two, indicates the sorting district within that zone. The final three digits are assigned to individual post offices within the sorting district.
